changes.name: Sales
changes.description: Income from any normal business activity

changes.name: Other Revenue
changes.description: Any other income that does not relate to normal business activities and is not recurring

changes.name: Interest Income
changes.description: Interest income

changes.name: Purchases
changes.description: Goods purchased with the intention of selling these to customers

changes.name: Cost of Goods Sold
changes.description: Cost of good sold by the business.

changes.name: Advertising
changes.description: Expenses incurred for advertising while trying to increase sales

changes.name: Bank Fees
changes.description: Fees charged by your bank for transactions regarding your bank account(s).

changes.name: Cleaning
changes.description: Expenses incurred for cleaning  business property.

changes.name: Consulting & Accounting
changes.description: Expenses related to paying consultants

changes.name: Depreciation
changes.description: The amount of the asset's cost (based on the useful life) that was consumed during the period

changes.name: Entertainment
changes.description: Expenses paid by company for the business but are not deductable for income tax purposes.

changes.name: Freight & Courier
changes.description: Expenses incurred on courier & freight costs

changes.name: General Expenses
changes.description: General expenses related to the running of the business.

changes.name: Insurance
changes.description: Expenses incurred for insuring the business' assets

changes.name: Interest Expense
changes.description: Any interest expenses paid to ATO, business bank accounts or credit card accounts.

changes.name: Legal expenses
changes.description: Expenses incurred on any legal matters

changes.name: Light, Power, Heating
changes.description: Expenses incurred for lighting, powering or heating the premises

changes.name: Motor Vehicle Expenses
changes.description: Expenses incurred on the running of company motor vehicles

changes.name: Office Expenses
changes.description: General expenses related to the running of the business office.

changes.name: Printing & Stationery
changes.description: Expenses incurred by the entity as a result of printing and stationery

changes.name: Rent
changes.description: The payment to lease a building or area.

changes.name: Repairs and Maintenance
changes.description: Expenses incurred on a damaged or run down asset that will bring the asset back to its original condition.

changes.name: Wages and Salaries
changes.description: Payment to employees in exchange for their resources

changes.name: Superannuation
changes.description: Superannuation contributions

changes.name: Commission
changes.description: Commission paid to staff in Payroll

changes.name: Subscriptions
changes.description: E.g. Magazines, professional bodies.

changes.name: Telephone & Internet
changes.description: Expenditure incurred from any business-related phone calls, phone lines, or internet connections

changes.name: Travel - National
changes.description: Expenses incurred from domestic travel which has a business purpose

changes.name: Travel - International
changes.description: Expenses incurred from international travel which has a business purpose

changes.name: Bank Revaluations
changes.description: Bank account revaluations due for foreign exchange rate changes

changes.name: Unrealised Currency Gains
changes.description: Unrealised currency gains on outstanding items

changes.name: Realised Currency Gains
changes.description: Gains or losses made due to currency exchange rate changes

changes.name: Income Tax Expense
changes.description: A percentage of total earnings paid to the government.

changes.name: Accounts Receivable
changes.description: Outstanding invoices the company has issued out to the client but has not yet received in cash at balance date.

changes.name: Prepayments
changes.description: An expenditure that has been paid for in advance.

changes.name: Inventory
changes.description: Value of tracked inventory items for resale.

changes.name: Office Equipment
changes.description: Office equipment that is owned and controlled by the business

changes.name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Office Equipment
changes.description: The total amount of office equipment cost that has been consumed by the entity (based on the useful life)

changes.name: Computer Equipment
changes.description: Computer equipment that is owned and controlled by the business

changes.name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Computer Equipment
changes.description: The total amount of computer equipment cost that has been consumed by the business (based on the useful life)

changes.name: Accounts Payable
changes.description: Outstanding invoices the company has received from suppliers but has not yet paid at balance date

changes.name: Unpaid Expense Claims
changes.description: Expense claims typically made by employees/shareholder employees still outstanding.

changes.name: Wage Payables
changes.description: Xero automatically updates this account for payroll entries created using Payroll and will store the payroll amount to be paid to the employee for the pay run. This account enables you to maintain separate accounts for employee Wages Payable amounts and Accounts Payable amounts

changes.name: GST
changes.description: The balance in this account represents GST owing to or from the ATO. At the end of the GST period, it is this account that should be used to code against either the 'refunds from' or 'payments to' the ATO that will appear on the bank statement. Xero has been designed to use only one GST account to track GST on income and expenses, so there is no need to add any new GST accounts to Xero.

changes.name: PAYG Withholdings Payable
changes.description: The amount of PAYE tax that is due to be paid

changes.name: Superannuation Payable
changes.description: The amount of superannuation that is due to be paid

changes.name: Income Tax Payable
changes.description: The amount of income tax that is due to be paid, also resident withholding tax paid on interest received.

changes.name: Revenue Received in Advance
changes.description: When a customer pays in advance of work/services.

changes.name: Historical Adjustment
changes.description: For accountant adjustments

changes.name: Suspense
changes.description: An entry that allows an unknown transaction to be entered, so the accounts can still be worked on in balance and the entry can be dealt with later.

changes.name: Rounding
changes.description: An adjustment entry to allow for rounding

changes.name: Tracking Transfers
changes.description: Transfers between tracking categories

changes.name: Owner A Drawings
changes.description: Withdrawals by the owners

changes.name: Owner A Funds Introduced
changes.description: Funds contributed by the owner

changes.name: Loan
changes.description: Money that has been borrowed from a creditor

changes.name: Retained Earnings
changes.description: Do not Use

changes.name: Owner A Share Capital
changes.description: The value of shares purchased by the shareholders
